  <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Ski Holidays in Passo Tonale</strong></p>
<p>Ski Passo Tonale! Book this season's skiing holiday in Passo Tonale and experience one of Italy's highest resorts. Passo Tonale sits in a wide, sunny valley on the border of Trento and Lombardy and with skiing on both the sunny south and north sides up on the Presena Glacier (3069m) it offers excellent snow-sure conditions.</p>
<p>Skiing holidays in Passo Tonale let you enjoy the resort's new 2 stage gondola which links Tonale's sunny wide slopes with a tree-lined run through the forest to the pretty village of Ponte di Legno, where more advanced runs are found. 5km of Cross country skiing are also available, with an additional 25km in Vermiglio the next village - a free bus is available.</p>
<p>Passo Tonale ski holidays offer a compact, friendly village with quick and easy access to the slopes, speedy queue-free lifts and the convenience of doorstep skiing. The resort has a warm and friendly atmosphere, with relaxed and lively après-ski bars.</p>
<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Passo Tonale</strong></p>
<p>Beginners and improvers find Tonale ideal. Group lessons begin on the sunny south-facing nursery slopes close to the village centre, and soon progress to the wide, higher runs above.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Passo Tonale</strong></p>
<p>Intermediates can tackle the sweeping 4.5km south-facing Alpina run to the village or the more challenging 11km run down to Ponte di Legno is not to be missed.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Passo Tonale</strong></p>
<p>A selection of off-pistes runs and a thrilling black run beneath the Paradiso cable-car.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Passo Tonale</strong></p>
<p>Snowboarders have a dedicated boarder park Snowpark (2000m) with kickers, boxes and rails and a Burton Progession Park. There are plenty of areas for off-piste and free-riding, great for skiers and boarders alike.</p>]]></description>
